name: Christian
review_text:
Entrei para um lanche rapido e sai com um prejuizo de 4000 Euros.

Esse Mc Donalds e ponto de pickpockets. Eles esperam voce se distrair para roubar sua bolsa, celular ou mochila. Furtaram minha mochila que tinha uma camera DSLR e acessorios, alem de todas as fotos da minha viagem. Nao ha seguranca nenhuma nesse lugar, mesmo com tantos casos relatados.

Evitem sentar especialmente nos bancos do segundo andar, eles consumam atuar nessa parte.
review_translated_text:
I went in for a quick snack and left with a loss of 4000 Euros.

This McDonald's is a pickpocket hotspot. They wait for you to get distracted to steal your purse, cell phone, or backpack. They stole my backpack which had a DSLR camera and accessories, as well as all the photos from my trip. There is absolutely no security in this place, even with so many reported cases.

Avoid sitting especially on the benches on the second floor; they tend to operate in that area.
response_from_owner_text: Lamentamos que tu experiencia no haya sido positiva, trasladamos tu feedback a nuestro departamento de calidad para que podamos seguir mejorando. Saludos.
response_from_owner_translated_text: We regret that your experience was not positive. We have forwarded your feedback to our quality department so we can continue to improve. Regards.

name: N
review_text:
Terrible experience, on one night I watched one chaotic employee playing around unhygienically across my 15 minute wait. In the kitchen area she play-wrestled her colleague choking them, licked their face, brushed her hand against the walls as she walked around, dropped a cardboard serving box on the floor but caught it with her shoe and then put it back ready for customer's food.... I saw her cooking fries after as well with no indication she washed her hands..

If this wasn't about food I wouldn't complain but this is unsafe and McDonald's have not responded to my report.

 Dicas: mantenha mochilas a frente do corpo, nao deixe bolsas nas cadeiras, feche os ziperes e redobre a atencao.

Alerta para evitar transtornos
review_translated_text:
ATTENTION PICKPOCKETS 
There are thefts of backpacks and belongings at the McDonald's across from Sagrada Familia, especially during peak hours.

 Tips: keep backpacks in front of your body, don't leave bags on chairs, close zippers, and be extra vigilant.

Alert to avoid problems

review_translated_text: I went to pick up an order today, and the guy who served me practically called me stupid to my face for asking about my order, which they hadn't mentioned and was right there on top of me with other bags. I half-complained about the treatment to a girl who seemed to be the manager, but they didn't care about the lack of respect. It seems that just because they work at McDonald's and not a 5-star restaurant, they can treat customers badly.

review_text:
This is more a location review than the food review.

Yeah, it's a McDonald's. About as good as a McDonald's can get in terms of food. We waited quite a long time for our smaller order and I suspect that's because it was prepared and promptly stolen. The girl serving orders did notice, took my receipt, and we recieved our meal shortly after. There was no mention of it being stolen, but it is a safe assumption based on other reviews

and it's no fault of the business, but my girlfriend and I couldn't finish our meal without being pestered by an annoying beggar who wouldn't take no for an answer. (and pretty evidently needed to go for a jog rather than to ask for more food) I had to shout and shoo them away in the end. ridiculous. Get your food and find somewhere else to sit other than this location

I keep my eyes on my belongings and on suspicious folk, and like other reviews mention, do so here. Swarming with bottom feeders

review_text:
Pues mala experiencia con la disque encargada, el ascensor no va y estoy con una persona con necesidad de utilizarlo.
Bueno el caso es que subio por las escaleras con ayuda de su hija  porque necesitaba ir al lavabo mientras yo me espero abajo con La sillas de ruedas mientras esta una chica tocando el boton de el ascensor a lo que le digo "no funciona" a lo que me responde de manera grosera "ya lo se yo trabajo aqui"(espanola)iba vestida normal por lo que pense era una persona que queria subir pero la manera imponente de responder muy desagradable me llevo una muy mala experiencia sobre todo su gesto y las formas....  Por otro lado si estaba una empleada que recogia bandejas muy muy amable y atenta(latina).

El bano para personas con silla de ruedas bastante sucio tambien.
review_translated_text:
Well, a bad experience with the so-called manager. The elevator isn't working, and I'm with someone who needs to use it.
Well, the fact is, she came up the stairs with the help of her daughter because she needed to go to the bathroom, while I waited downstairs with the wheelchair. A woman was pressing the elevator button, to which I told her "it's not working." She rudely responded, "I know, I work here." (She's Spanish). She was dressed normally, so I thought she was someone who wanted to get on the elevator. But her imposing, very unpleasant way of responding left me with a very bad experience, especially her gesture and manner. On the other hand, there was an employee collecting trays, very, very kind and attentive (Latina).
In short, a very unpleasant situation.
The wheelchair-accessible bathroom was also quite dirty.

name: hercios1
review_text:
He estado en muchos McDonald's, pero este ha sido sin duda uno de los peores. La comida la preparan sin el mas minimo cuidado: todo mal presentado, como si lo tiraran dentro de la caja sin mirar. Da la sensacion de que la cocina va con prisas, sin carino ni profesionalidad.

El local, ademas, es un caos. Esta completamente masificado, apenas hay sitio para moverse y encontrar una mesa libre es mision imposible. Tienes que quedarte de pie esperando a que alguien termine de comer para poder sentarte, y mientras tanto, todo abarrotado, ruidoso y sin ninguna organizacion.

Para colmo, el sitio es muy pequeno para la cantidad de gente que entra. No da abasto ni para atender bien ni para que la experiencia sea medianamente agradable. Una pena, porque uno viene buscando algo rapido y comodo... y se encuentra con todo lo contrario.
review_translated_text:
I've been to many McDonald's, but this has undoubtedly been one of the worst. The food is prepared with absolutely no care: everything is poorly presented, as if they just threw it in the box without a second thought. It feels like the kitchen is rushed, lacking any care or professionalism.

The place itself is also chaotic. It's completely overcrowded, there's barely room to move, and finding a free table is mission impossible. You have to stand waiting for someone to finish eating before you can sit down, and in the meantime, everything is packed, noisy, and disorganized.

To top it all off, the place is far too small for the number of people who go in. It can't handle the volume to provide decent service or even a remotely pleasant experience. It's a shame, because you come looking for something quick and convenient... and you find the complete opposite.

Nous avons bien mange, comme on peut s'y attendre de cette chaine, mais nous avons ete decus par l'etat du restaurant. Non seulement il etait tres vieillot, mais il etait egalement extremement sale.
Les tables et les sols n'etaient pas nettoyes correctement, ce qui a vraiment gache l'experience.
Malgre cela, la nourriture et le service etaient satisfaisants, c'est pourquoi je laisse tout de meme une note correcte, meme si le cadre et la proprete laissent grandement a desirer.
review_translated_text:
I recently visited a McDonald's in Spain.
We had a good meal, as you'd expect from this chain, but we were disappointed by the condition of the restaurant. Not only was it very dated, but it was also extremely dirty.
The tables and floors weren't cleaned properly, which really spoiled the experience.
Despite this, the food and service were satisfactory, so I'm still giving it a decent rating, even though the setting and cleanliness leave a lot to be desired.
response_from_owner_text: Gracias por tu feedback Sylvain, nos ayuda a mejorar nuestros restaurantes. Te esperamos de nuevo en McDonald's.

Un dia fui con una amiga y en un pedido le pusieron pepinillos sin haberlos pedido y no le pusieron la salsa que habia comprado.

Decepcionada del servicio de los empleados, el peor mcdonalds al que he acudido.
review_translated_text:
The atmosphere was awful. There's only one floor, it's always packed, and it's incredibly noisy. Being a McDonald's near the Sagrada Familia, the staffing was terrible. There was only one person at the register. I had scanned a deal, and they made me wait for over 15 minutes until it expired, and then I had to scan it again.
One day I went with a friend, and they added pickles to her order without her having asked for them, and they didn't include the sauce she had purchased.

I'm very disappointed with the service. It's the worst McDonald's I've ever been to.
response_from_owner_text: Todo el equipo de McDonald's Barcelona agradece vuestras valoraciones, nos ayuda a mejorar.

name: Alex Lase
review_text:
La verdad que McDonald's cada vez mas insulso. La comida nunca fue la gran cosa, pero ahora las papas se siente que tienen menos gusto, las hamburguesas siempre las entregan como si fuera un choque de tren (la hamburguesa por un lado, el queso por el otro), el pan da tristeza, y estoy convencido de que el cuarto de libra tiene menos queso que nunca.
Pedimos la orden a la mesa y tardaron mucho mas que para aquellos que pedian de mostrador o los de delivery. La limpieza en este local suele ser muy pobre, es dificil encontrar una mesa que no este totalmente pegoteada.
review_translated_text:
Honestly, McDonald's is getting more and more bland. The food was never great, but now the fries feel less flavorful, the burgers are always delivered like a train wreck (the burger on one side, the cheese on the other), the bun is sad, and I'm convinced the Quarter Pounder has less cheese than ever.
We ordered at the table, and it took much longer than for those who ordered at the counter or for delivery. Cleanliness at this location is usually very poor; it's hard to find a table that isn't completely covered in grease.
response_from_owner_text: Vaya... sentimos mucho tu experiencia en nuestro McDonald's de Barcelona, Alex. Cuentanos tu experiencia en atencionconsumidor@es.mcd.com.En McDonald's siempre velamos siempre por la salud de nuestros clientes, trabajadores y colaboradores. !Esperamos que vuelvas pronto!

At McDonald's, we always take care of the health of our customers, employees, and partners. We hope you come back soon!

name: Helena Jurado
review_text:
Habia mucha gente y era temporada de turistas, pero aun asi se nos sirvio rapido a mi pareja y a mi. La comida es exactamente igual que cualquier otro restaurante de la misma cadena en Espana, de calidad regular pero con un sabor muy bueno.
Cuando fue hora de recoger nuestros McFlurry, se equivocaron en el mio poniendole otro sirope. Se lo explique a la chica y muy amablemente me dijo que lo sentia mucho y me hizo otro con el doble de todo (helado, sirope y topping). Adjunto una foto de esto. El mejor McFlurry que he comido.
Ademas, durante toda nuestra comida iba pasando un chico limpiando y preguntandonos si estaba todo bien. Nos pusieron una salsa de menos y sin poner pegas ni nada nos dio dos mas. Me encanto el servicio.
review_translated_text:
It was busy and peak tourist season, but my partner and I were still served quickly. The food is exactly the same as any other restaurant in the same chain in Spain--average quality, but very tasty.
When it was time to pick up our McFlurries, they made a mistake with mine, putting the wrong syrup on it. I explained this to the girl, and she very kindly apologized and made me another one with double everything (ice cream, syrup, and toppings). I've attached a photo. The best McFlurry I've ever had.
Also, throughout our meal, a guy kept coming around cleaning and asking if everything was okay. They gave us one sauce too few, and without any fuss, he gave us two more. I loved the service.

name: Jacob
review_text:
Words can't describe how abysmal my service at this location was...

Just ate here and I absolutely hated it. I ordered my food at around 2:45 and the machine said to pay at the till, so I assumed that meant the food would be prepared and I'd have to pay to collect it... So I waited and the food didn't even show up on the screen: apparently you had to go to a separate till to order the food once you ordered it??? Even after I paid, the food still didn't show up on the screen.

30 minutes went by and my food STILL hadn't shown up on the screen, so I tried asking one of the employees if they got my order and they just looked at me and shook their head as if I were being impatient. My order was number 20 and by this point orders in the 50s were being collected.

I stood there for another 20 minutes, trying to catch the attention of the staff to ask where the actual -- my order was, as there was STILL no sign that was food was being prepared. At this point, I noticed a drink with the number 20 on just sat there, seemingly there for the whole time... With the lid off. HOW UNHYGIENIC. (The photo attached is my drink sat on the side as described) Finally, after over an hour, the staff called out number 20. Except it wasn't MY order 20, I realised that they had gone through all 100 orders and back to the start again, so it was someone else's food. It took this confusion to make the staff finally act and begin preparing my order, 1 HOUR AFTER I ORDERED IT!!! I literally had the order time on the receipt which proved how long I had waited for the food. There is quite literally no excuse as to why they took 1 hour to even start on my food, as 100 people who ordered after me got theirs first. It's not like I ordered 100 big macs or anything ridiculous, I literally just ordered a regular meal, and so did everyone else. I would understand if the place was absolutely heaving and none of my friends got their order, but they all ordered around the same time as me and got theirs almost straight away. The preparing list consistently only had 2 or 3 meals on it too which shows that barely anyone was ordering anything.

The staff were extremely rude throughout the whole thing. One of them looked at me when I said that I hadn't received my order and then ran off, another shook their head at me as described before. As far as I'm aware, they didn't even apologise for the 1 hour wait.

When I actually received the food the quality was low. The drink that was left on the side for 1 hour completely lost its fizziness and not long after drinking it I had a stomach bug. My drink didn't even come with a straw!!! The rest was fairly plain and not at all worth the artificial one-hour wait.

The location is poor, with a severe lack of seats compared to the number of customers. I found myself sharing a table with a random family while waiting for my order, which then took an hour to come and I had an event I had to attend so I had to take out when it finally arrived. There is an upstairs floor, which consists of a grand total of 2 tables!!!

Would genuinely give this zero or negative stars if I could, but I'm definitely not coming back here, considering it can't even serve food; its ONE JOB!!!  There are far better restaurants to visit in Barcelona.

name: Angela Perez Leal
review_text: Entiendo que trabajar en un mcdonals junto a la Sagrada Familia tiene que ser agotador, pero se verdad que la actitud de la encargada y la chica que traia la comida a las mesas es lamentable. Te amargan la hamburguesa. Habiendo pagado dos salsas y dos ketchups extra, casi que me escupen por solicitarla en barra. Y no contesta, la encargada detras mia para ver en el tickets que de verdad lo habia pagado. Luego la chica que traia la comida a las mesas arrastrando los pies y literalmente nos tiro la bandeja a la mesa, derramando parte de la bebida, la cual no traia ni tapa (ok, comemos aqui, no la necesito) ni pajita, la cual ni me atrevi a pedir por no verle la cara de nuevo a la de la barra. Lamentable...
review_translated_text: I understand that working at a McDonald's next to the Sagrada Familia must be exhausting, but it's true that the attitude of the manager and the girl who brought the food to the tables is deplorable. They make your burger sour. Having paid for two extra sauces and two ketchups, they almost spit on me for asking for it at the bar. And the manager behind me didn't answer to check the receipt that I had actually paid for it. Then the girl who brought the food to the tables shuffled and literally threw the tray on the table, spilling part of the drink, which didn't even come with a lid (okay, we're eating here, I don't need one) or a straw, which I didn't even dare ask for because I didn't want to see the bartender's face again. Pathetic...

review_translated_text: I usually don't write reviews, but I ordered a hamburger set and a McNugget, and even though they didn't have a lot on the menu, they left out the McNuggets. Even though two employees double-checked the receipt and the contents of the paper bag before I received my food, the McNuggets were still missing. In a country like Spain, and especially at McDonald's, a global company, racial discrimination is not tolerated, but it seems like something to be careful about. It wasn't even 1988. Do they do this in an EU country? Oh, and of course, they left out the McNuggets in Lisbon too.
response_from_owner_text: !Hola Konl! Te agradecemos tus palabras, para ayudarnos a seguir mejorando puedes contarnos mas detalles en atencionconsumidor@es.mcd.com. !Gracias!

name: Krol Benitez
review_text:
Este McDonalds esta muy bien ubicado, con mucho espacio para consumir. Tienen wifi.
La hamburguesa como siempre rica, un poco cara por el tamano de los productos.
El lugar siempre esta lleno.
El personal algunas veces es amable y otras no tanto.
review_translated_text:
This McDonald's is very well located, with plenty of space to eat. They have Wi-Fi.
The burgers are delicious, as always, a little pricey given the size of the items.
The place is always packed.
The staff is sometimes friendly, other times not so much.

review_translated_text: Terrible service. We ordered online, they forgot a menu, and they responded rudely, telling us to notify the shipping company. Terrible... it's a shame that a franchise of such a major company is capable of providing such poor service.

name: Mario M
review_text:
Mi hijo queria el juguete de Pokemon que anunciaban, lo ofertan en el mostrador, lo ofertan en el panel de auto pedido y lo tienen en la vitrina expuesto como promocion activa. Resulta que no lo tienen y quieren que la gente se entere con un cartelito enano que no se ve con la gente haciendo cola para pedir.

Si no lo tienen lo suyo es poner lo que estan regalando y no haciendo publicidad enganosa con otra promocion.
review_translated_text:
My son wanted the Pokemon toy they were advertising. They're offering it at the counter, on the self-order panel, and have it displayed in the window as an active promotion. It turns out they don't have it, and they want people to know with a tiny little sign that can't be seen with people queuing up to order.

If they don't have it, the best thing to do is to list what they're giving away, not engage in misleading advertising with another promotion.

name: FRANCISCO DIAZ
review_text:
He pedido un cafe americano, como hago habitualmente. Me han servido un cafe en un tamano mini y la unica explicacion: es el vaso mas grande que tienen.
Ya no digo que me lo sirvan en una taza de MC coffe como en otras ocasiones pero si en su tamano estandar.
Por estar en frente de la sagrada familia no tienen porque reducir ni la calidad ni la cantidad.
review_translated_text: I ordered an Americano, as usual. They served me a mini coffee, and the only explanation they gave was that it was the largest cup they had. I'm not saying they should serve it in a McCoffe mug like they do on other occasions, but at least in a standard size. Just because they're across from the Sagrada Familia doesn't mean they have to reduce either the quality or the quantity.

review_text: Servicio malo, un simple menu de tostada con tomate tuve que volver a por el aceite y sal al llegar en mostrador me dijeron que traiga de nuevo mi pedido para ver si realmente faltan el aceite y sal  la encargada se llevo mis tostadas y volvio al final me dio el aceite solo sin sal y nuse k hizo dentro al coger mis tostadas espero que no hizo nada con ellos
review_translated_text: Bad service, a simple toast with tomato menu. I had to go back for the oil and salt. When I got to the counter, they told me to bring my order again to see if the oil and salt were really missing  The manager took my toast and came back. In the end, she gave me just the oil without salt, and I don't know what she did inside when she took my toast. I hope she didn't do anything with them

name: Hansen Loke
review_text:
Thought I'd sample the McD in Barcelona with my family to compare with other McD in other countries. I ordered a Big Mac. The burger was nearly arranged, the tidiest Big Mac assembled I've seen. Yet something was not quite right. A couple of bites into the burger revealed it was less than warm and the middle bun and patty slipped right out, leaving one patty behind like a magic trick. The bun and meat were dry and salad in burger was slightly wet, which is probably the reason for the now-you-see the middle section and now-you-don't.

The price for the burger alone is much higher than London even after converosion rate. Guess that's why they call it the Big Mac factor when comparing the economies.

The service was great. Relatively quick given the queues. The attendant noticed there were two trays when I went to pick it up and offered to hold one of them till I came back for the second trip.

name: Claudia Vergotti
review_text: Pequeno McDonalds situado justo al lado de la Sagrada Familia. El local es muy pequeno por la zona en la que se encuentra y hay pocas mesas. En la parte de arriba solo hay aseos (bastante limpios). Tardaron muchisimo en prepararnos la comida, y el local no estaba lleno, fuimos a las 20. Pero el personal fue muy amable y disponibles, pedimos ayuda para poder cargar el movil y nos dejaron cargarlo sin problema.
review_translated_text: A small McDonald's located right next to the Sagrada Familia. The restaurant is very small, given its location, and there are only a few tables. There are only restrooms upstairs (quite clean). It took them ages to prepare our food, and the restaurant wasn't busy; we went at 8 p.m. However, the staff was very friendly and helpful. We asked for help charging our phone, and they let us charge it without any problem.
response_from_owner_text: En McDonald's valoramos mucho tu comentario, nos motiva a seguir trabajando a diario por ofrecer lo mejor de nosotros. !Que tengas un buen dia!

name: Zuzanna Ciesla
review_text: Wir waren dort am 23.08.22 . Die Security war sehr nett. Die Mitarbeitern an der Kasse gar nicht. Wir haben bestellt und auch alles bekommen obwohl kein vegi Burger zu kaufen gabt. Da aktuell eine Aktion vin Mc lauft mit Gewinnmoglichkeit haben wir eine Apfel Schnitte und Pommes gewonnen. Ich bin zur Kasse gegangen und die zwei Coupon der Mitarbeiterin gegeben na ca 20 min warten und nachfragen wurde ich garnicht beachtet. Ich bin einfach enttauscht gegangen die Gewinne waren mir nich Wert langer zu warten und sich zu argern. Traurig dass man so behandelt wird.
review_translated_text: We were there on August 23, 2022. The security guards were very friendly. The cashiers, however, were not. We ordered and received everything, even though there were no vegetarian burgers available. Since McDonald's was running a promotion with a chance to win, we won an apple slice and fries. I went to the cashier and gave the two coupons to the cashier. After waiting for about 20 minutes and asking about it, I was completely ignored. I simply left disappointed; the prizes weren't worth the extra wait and frustration. It's sad to be treated like that.
response_from_owner_text: Muchas gracias por tu opinion, Zuzanna. ?Puedes contarnos mas sobre lo ocurrido en atencionconsumidor@es.mcd.com? Para McDonald's es muy importante que tengas una buena experiencia en nuestros restaurantes y gracias a tu valoracion podremos seguir mejorando.

review_text: Tienen una cobertura penosa dentro del local, el wifi tampoco les va, pero si no puedes pedir, te dicen que es culpa de tu aplicacion. Es solo para pagar a menos personal, pero tampoco te rebajan el menu por hacerlo tu todo. Vamos una pena que cada dia funcionen peor, encima pides una hoja de reclamacion por el trato que te dan y te dicen que si quieres puedes hablar con el encargado...
review_translated_text: The phone coverage inside the restaurant is terrible, the Wi-Fi doesn't work either, but if you can't order, they tell you it's your app's fault. Excuse me... the app isn't mine, and having to order from machines instead of being served by a person isn't my problem either. It's just a way to pay fewer staff, but they don't even give you a discount for doing everything yourself. It's a shame they're getting worse every day. On top of that, you ask for a complaint form about the way they treat you, and they tell you that you can talk to the manager if you want...

name: Kathleen
review_text:
Wahnsinnig uberfullt, da die Mitarbeiter mit den Bestellungen absolut nicht hinterher kommen, vermutlich weil sie alle SEHR langsam arbeiten. Keine Servietten, kaum Sitzplatze. Zusatzlich wurde uns dort der Rucksack geklaut, war den Mitarbeitern komplett egal. Der Schichtleiter (oder Chef?) war nicht mal bereit mit uns zu reden.!!! PASST AUF EURE SACHEN AUF, die Taschendiebe dort sind gerissen. Wir hatten im Rucksack zwei Ausweise, mussten am Flughafen Ersatzdokumente holen und direkt vor uns spater am Check-in waren drei Frauen, denen genau das selbe am gleichen Tag am gleichen Ort passiert ist.
Um die Sagrada Familia rum am besten alle Wertsachen dicht an Korper und die Handys nicht in der Hosentasche haben! Hat uns leider einen schonen Tag komplett versaut.
review_translated_text:
Incredibly crowded, as the staff absolutely cannot keep up with the orders, probably because they all work VERY slowly. No napkins, hardly any seating. On top of that, our backpack was stolen, but the staff didn't care at all. The shift supervisor (or boss?) wasn't even willing to talk to us!!! WATCH YOUR BELONGINGS, the pickpockets there are cunning. We had two IDs in our backpack, had to get replacement documents at the airport, and later at check-in there were three women right in front of us who had the exact same thing happen to them on the same day at the same place.

Around the Sagrada Familia, it's best to keep all valuables close to your body and your cell phones out of your pockets! Unfortunately, it completely ruined a lovely day for us.
response_from_owner_text: Muchas gracias por tu opinion, Kathleen. ?Puedes contarnos mas sobre lo ocurrido en atencionconsumidor@es.mcd.com? Para McDonald's es muy importante que tengas una buena experiencia en nuestros restaurantes y gracias a tu valoracion podremos seguir mejorando.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you very much for your feedback, Kathleen. Could you please tell us more about what happened at atencionconsumidor@es.mcd.com? It's very important to McDonald's that you have a good experience in our restaurants, and thanks to your feedback, we can continue to improve.

Por ser un lugar lleno de turista la atencion es fantastica y muy rapida no paran un segundo .
Lo que si me molesto mucho y mas en estos tiempos es que el encargado un hombre mayor( de pelo blanco y sentado muy comodo) les gritaba y de muy mala manera les explicaba como hacer lo que el consideraba que estaba mal , este comportamiento violento de parte de este dinosaurio no deberia existir mas,  espero que le den salida y pongan a alguien mas humano , lo demas genial .
review_translated_text:
For a place full of tourists, the service is fantastic and very fast, they don't stop for a second.
What really bothered me, especially these days, is that the manager, an older man (with white hair and sitting very comfortably), yelled at them and rudely explained how to do what he considered wrong. This violent behavior from this dinosaur should no longer exist. I hope they get rid of him and hire someone more humane. Everything else is great.
response_from_owner_text: Muchas gracias por tus palabras joaquin, con clientes como tu es todo mas facil. !Te esperamos pronto!
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you so much for your kind words, Joaquin. With clients like you, everything is easier. We hope to see you again soon!

En cuanto a las patatas fritas, unicamente se conservan 7 minutos. Esperamos volver a verte pronto!
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you for your review, Gergo. We'd like to remind you that at McDonald's, we also take great care to ensure the freshness of our burgers; if they aren't served within 10 minutes, they are removed from sale. As for the fries, they are only kept for 7 minutes. We hope to see you again soon!

review_text: Muy limpio. y de lo pocas lugares con Wi Fi Gratis en Barcelona
review_translated_text: Very clean. And one of the few places with free Wi-Fi in Barcelona.

name: C G
review_text:
Peor servicio que pueda existir. Hemos pedido mil veces por glovo y no hay dia que hagan correctamente el pedido. En todos los que he hecho siempre ha faltado algun producto. Este ultimo he pagado 25EU por unos nuggets y una hamburguesa, se han olvidado de anadir las alitas, el helado y la bebida, y eso que les aparece todo en el ticket. Encima cuando llamas al establecimiento no hay manera de que cojan el telefono.
Vergonozoso.
review_translated_text: The worst service imaginable. We've ordered through Glovo a thousand times, and not a single day has they gotten the order right. Every single time, something has been missing. This last time, I paid EU25 for nuggets and a burger, but they forgot to add the wings, ice cream, and drink, even though everything is listed on the receipt. And to top it all off, when you call the restaurant, they never answer the phone. Shameful.

name: Marc Iniesta Sune
review_text: Siempre que pido a traves de Glovo se dejan un par de complementos por lo menos, ya se que se puede reclamar y glovo devuelve el dinero, pero solo quiero que hagais bien vuestro trabajo
review_translated_text: Whenever I order through Glovo, they leave at least a couple of extras. I know that I can complain and Glovo will refund the money, but I just want you to do your job well.

name: Shaline
review_text: Von MC Donalds erwartet man ja so schon nicht viel aber komplett kaltes Essen zu erhalten ist eine Zumutung. Zudem gibt es nicht mal Servietten...
review_translated_text: You don't expect much from McDonald's to begin with, but receiving completely cold food is unacceptable. And they don't even have napkins...

name: lollodrumDJ

review_text: Muchos humanos en un espacio muy cerrado. M dio ansidad casi m da un atake d panico. La dependienta muy maja. Le pedi el insta pero no me lo dio pero fue muy respetuosa. Asi da gusto que te rechazen. Volveria
review_translated_text: Too many people in a very enclosed space. It gave me anxiety, almost panicked. The clerk was very nice. I asked for her Instagram number, but she didn't give it to me, but she was very respectful. It's a pleasure to be rejected. I'd come back.

name: Manuel Munoz Prieto
review_text:
Lo mejor la atencion del personal, muy atentos y amables.
Recomendado.

The best part was the staff's attention; they were very attentive and friendly.
Highly recommended.

Pesima experiencia

Terrible experience!
Unlike other McDonald's, the burgers were dry and rushed...dry and undercooked!

review_text: una verguenza pagas un menu y ni te lo ponen hay teneis la prueba el tiket y lo que me han puesta y no es la primera vez que me pasa ya son 3 veces estoy arta ara aver si me devuelven los 8 euros un servicio pesimo en sagrada familia
review_translated_text: It's a disgrace, you pay for a menu and they don't even serve it to you. Here you have the proof: the ticket and what they served me. And it's not the first time it's happened to me. It's already been 3 times. I'm fed up. I'll see if they'll give me back the 8 euros. Terrible service at the Sagrada Familia.

name: Ricardo Bonnet
review_text: He ordenado a traves de la maquina y al cobrarme al dia siguiente he visto que han hecho dos cobros. Cuando he reclamado, la chica de camisa blanca que atiende en la caja me ha dicho que reclame al banco. Lo he hecho y desde el banco me dijeron que ha sido la tienda que hay realizado el cobro. Al final, pague doble y comi una sola vez.
review_translated_text: I ordered through the machine, and when I checked out the next day, I saw that they'd charged me twice. When I complained, the girl in a white shirt at the register told me to complain to the bank. I did, and the bank told me it was the store that charged me. In the end, I paid twice and only ate once.

name: Taysha Valencia
review_text: La comida bien pero se equivocan a veces en mi pedido se han olvidado de varias cosas y tenia prisa :((
review_translated_text: The food was good, but they sometimes make mistakes with my order; they forgot several things and I was in a hurry :((

review_translated_text: Add veggie burgers, and you'll allow non-meat eaters to eat something other than chips, coffee, ice cream, or cardboard salads. Bathroom hygiene isn't usually very good either.

name: victorr marti gotor
review_text:
Gran experiencia la verdad que saben hacer las cosas, incluso dias con el local lleno y el delivery tambien lleno lo sacan bastante rapido, al final es lo que uno busca en restaurantes de comida rapida.
La cheseburger sensacional
review_translated_text:
A great experience. They really know how to do things. Even on days when the restaurant is packed and the delivery service is also full, they get it done pretty quickly. In the end, it's what you look for in fast food restaurants.
The Cheeseburger is sensational.

name: Ivo Matos
review_text: Good location, employees could work faster

You leave out a product, the Gouda Cheese Bites, for EU3.55 less, and I call, call, and call the restaurant, and you don't pick up. Who do I contact? The Madrid number you have at Just Eat? You're very poorly managed. Seriously, you're very thick-skinned. They couldn't provide me with any help, not even telephone assistance, and I'm left with a delayed and incomplete order. name: Eduard Carol Perez
review_text:
Decepcionado con la hamburgesa Hacia tiempo que no ibamos pero a mi hija le hacia gracia el happy meal y tubimos que ir alli en vez de a otro sitio.
PROs:
Local limpio
Personal atento y educado.
Muy rapido.
El helado muy bueno.
Mucho menos plastico que la ultima vez.
CONTRAs
La hamburgesa visualmente era muy poco apetecible comparado con la foto de la pantalla donde pedimos. De sabor tampoco era nada del otro mundo.
El refresco es 50% hielo, 50& cola
Las patatas deluxe secas que hubiesemos necesitado 10 sobres de ketchup para bajarlas.
13,5 euros por eso, es un robo.
review_translated_text:
Disappointed with the burger. It had been a while since we'd been there, but my daughter was keen on the Happy Meal, so we had to go there instead of somewhere else.

PROs:
Clean place.
Attentive and polite staff.
Very fast.
The ice cream was very good.
Much less plastic than last time.

CONs:
The burger looked very unappetizing compared to the picture on the screen where we ordered. The taste wasn't anything special either.
The soft drink was 50% ice, 50% cola.
The deluxe fries were so dry we would have needed 10 packets of ketchup to wash them down.
EU13.50 for that is a rip-off.

review_translated_text: I was extremely disappointed with the McFlurry. It had been ages since I'd had one, and trying it again was a terrible experience. There was hardly any ice cream or syrup, and the topping was awful. I ordered the Suchard one, and they just put powder on it. I don't recommend it.

review_text: Un sitio muy tradicional para comer comida rapida  hamburguesas. Estan bastante buenas y son baratas. El problema es que hay mucha gente (turistas), y las hamburguesas (solo la carne) no son de buena calidad. tambien cuando pides algun topping son muy tacanos, y te ponen muy poco. Si quieres anadir un topping extra vale 0,50EU, y te siguen poniendo muy poco. Vale la pena comprar un postre, recomiendo los McFlurris.
review_translated_text: A very traditional place for fast food burgers. They're quite good and cheap. The problem is that there are a lot of people (tourists), and the burgers (just the meat) aren't good quality. Also, when you ask for a topping, they're very stingy and give you very little. If you want to add an extra topping, it costs EU0.50, and they still give you very little. It's worth getting a dessert; I recommend the McFlurris.

review_text:
Estuve de mochilero unos dias en Espana y el McTrio (bueno, asi lo conocemos en Mexico) de hamburguesa triple con queso, papas y refresco a EU5 realmente fue una maravilla. Yo se que ir desde otro pais a comer lo mismo que hay en el tuyo no es lo mejor, pero gracias a ese ahorro pude pagar entradas a lugares geniales.
El lugar limpio, y la atencion buena, aunque tienen el servicio de que tu eliges todo en una pantalla y solo recoges tu pedido.
review_translated_text: I was backpacking in Spain for a few days, and the McTrio (well, that's what we call it in Mexico) of a triple cheeseburger, fries, and a soft drink for EU5 was truly amazing. I know that traveling from another country to eat the same food as back home isn't ideal, but thanks to that money, I was able to pay for entry to some great places. The place was clean, and the service was good, although they do have a system where you choose everything on a screen and just pick up your order.

review_text:
Vivo a tres calles del restaurante, cuando hago delivery jamas me viene completo. Hace mucho que no pedia por que se que son un desastre. Hoy ha vuelto a decepcionarme. Hace una hora pedi un menu y un helado. Me encarnaria cancelar el pedido pero encima me lo cobraran. En la competencia nunca me pasa estas cosas. Tienen un gran problema y les da igual solucionarlo, esto no viene de hace poco.
Espero no perder la memoria y no pedirles nada mas.
Ojala pudiera pedir de otro restaurante y no de este!!!
review_translated_text:
I live three blocks from the restaurant, and when I order delivery, it never comes complete. I haven't ordered from them in ages because I know they're terrible. Today they disappointed me again. An hour ago, I ordered a meal and an ice cream. I'd hate to cancel the order, but on top of that, they'll charge me. This never happens to me at the competition. They have a huge problem and they don't care about fixing it; this isn't a recent issue.
I hope I don't forget and never order from them again. I wish I could order from another restaurant instead of this one!

Comimos al mediodia  del domingo 27, y trato desagradable del personal. Ni manejar el sistema de pedidos solo aceptan ese medio. Hacen mal el pedido de una comida sin gluten y encima te discute. La encargada de la caja al medio dia que nos atendio precisa educacion y formas. Hasta ese dia no habia conocido tan mal servicio en est cadena que usamos frecuentemente.
Recomiendo reciclar personal espero que esto valga para algo y si esa cajera esta quemada que se largue.
review_translated_text:
We ate at noon on Sunday the 27th, and the staff treated us unpleasantly. They couldn't even manage the ordering system; they only accept that method. They misunderstood the gluten-free order and then argued with you. The cashier at noon who served us needed politeness and manners. Until that day, I hadn't experienced such poor service at this chain, which we frequent.
I recommend retraining staff. I hope this helps. If that cashier is burned out, she should leave.

Son muy agiles los empleados y me gusto mucho que velan por el cuidado del cliente , al devolverme el cambio yo estaba ocupada en ese momento y la chica puso la bandeja dentro para que no me fueran a quitar el cambio mientras yo llegaba a la caja de nuevo.

Fue muy considerada y me gusto esa accion asi que les doy cinco estrellas muchas gracias.
review_translated_text:
Ideal for going with kids. The service is fast. You can place your order on the screen, and they'll help you with cash or card payments. The order is very fast, and the bathrooms are very clean, ideal for going with little ones.

The employees are very responsive, and I really liked that they take care of the customer. When I gave them my change, I was busy at the time, and the girl put the tray inside so they wouldn't take my change while I got back to the register.

She was very considerate, and I liked that action, so I give them five stars. Thank you very much.

Imagine our surprise when we saw they hadn't given us the "deluxe" fries she ordered! They gave us regular fries instead. My poor son was so upset when he saw they'd made a mistake. The receipt says "deluxe."
Please don't make so many mistakes, thank you.

La encargada de esta tienda no tiene modales y menos don de gente, ha salido gritando y manoteando por NO entender una situacion de una mesa en protocolos COVID, la pobre empleada que gestionaba la situacion de aforo se quedo paralizada al ver tal actitud (asi sera...), todo un show frente a clientes y con un nino...

Lo que si pareceria era que resguardaba las mesas cercanas a su hijo o familiar con un grupo amiguitos, ya que un peque entraba a cocina como si fuese la de su casa, cosa que no deberia por medidas de higiene.
review_translated_text:
The manager of this store has no manners, much less people skills. She came out screaming and waving her hands because she didn't understand a table situation regarding COVID protocols. The poor employee managing the capacity situation froze when she saw such behavior (that's how it is...), quite a spectacle in front of customers and with a child...

What it seemed like was that she was protecting the tables near her child or a family member with a group of friends, since a little one was entering the kitchen as if it were her own home, which she shouldn't be doing due to hygiene measures.

Lo unico malo las patatas del happy meal que estaban un poco frias.

name: Malaika Saleem
review_text:
Ayer planee ir a cenar en Mc de sagrada familia teniendo en cuenta q sali a las 12.30h tenia calculado la hora de cierre y llegue 13 min antes de q cerraran. Llegue a las 12.47 entre en el local y la chica me paro en la puerta negando a servirme, le ensene la hora q aun me quedan 13min y me dijo q no pq con las 4 chicos q ya estaban dentro ya era suficiente y q no podeia a llegar a pedir. Yo mu y amablemente le dije dejame hacer la cola si hasta la una y si no me llega a atender me ire. Bueno lo acceptable. Igual la chica me nego a atender teniendo en cuanta q aun quedaban 13 min. Mc es una cadena de comida rapida yo no iba a estar ahi con un entrante, principal, postre y cafe.
En fin ademas la chica me dice q me vaya a bueger king q estan abiertos q tambien cerraban a la 1. Bueno yo tenia hambre y me fui y cuando llego eso ya estaba cerrado. Estoy muy peeo muy molestada por el comportamiento de la chica y su falta de interes en su trabajo. Si cierran a la una pues es a la 1, no a las 1 menos 13.
review_translated_text: Yesterday, I planned to go to dinner at McLaren's in Sagrada Familia, keeping in mind that I left at 12:30 p.m. I had calculated the closing time, and I arrived 13 minutes before closing time. I arrived at 12:47 p.m. I entered the restaurant, and the girl stopped me at the door, refusing to serve me. I showed her the time and said I still had 13 minutes left, and she said no because with the four guys already inside, it was enough and I couldn't make it to order. I very politely told her, "Let me wait in line until 1:00 p.m.," and if she didn't serve me, I'd leave. It was acceptable. The girl still refused to serve me, considering I still had 13 minutes left. McLaren is a fast-food chain, so I wasn't going to be there with a starter, main course, dessert, and coffee. Anyway, the girl also told me to go to Burger King, which is open and also closes at 1:00. Well, I was hungry so I left, and when I got back, it was already closed. I'm really, really annoyed by the girl's behavior and her lack of interest in her job. If they close at 1:00, then it's 1:00, not 1:13.

review_text: Mi pedido se realizo por Uber. En el menu las patatas deluxe estaban pasadas,las patatas normales estaban pasadas de temperatura y duras, la hamburguesa estaba muy dura. No ponen ni servilletas ni canitas para la bebida ni ketchup ni salsa deluxe cuando son dos menus con patatas. Lo mas fuerte esque el helado era un oreo con extra de chocolate y no habian apenas chocolate.. una barbaridad pero no es la primera Vez que este restaurante realiza un mal servicio de la calidad de la comida y de los detalles..El servicio es pesimo y pienso que tendrian que pensar en mirar de cambiar la calidad de sus servicios porque no esta la altura de una cadena de restauracion.
review_translated_text: My order was placed through Uber. The deluxe fries on the menu were overcooked, the regular fries were overcooked and hard, and the burger was very tough. They don't provide napkins, straws, ketchup, or deluxe sauce, even though there are two meals with fries. The worst thing is that the ice cream was an Oreo with extra chocolate, and there was barely any chocolate... It's outrageous, but it's not the first time this restaurant has provided poor service, considering the quality of the food and the attention to detail. The service is terrible, and I think they should consider improving the quality of their service because it's not up to par with a restaurant chain.

review_translated_text: I'm giving the Sagrada Familia McDonald's one star for taking a quarter-pounder from the bin and removing the pickle from the burger, which I saw with my own eyes. The kitchen manager claimed it was freshly taken out, even though the cheese was melted and had been in the bin for quite some time. This was to cover for the kitchen employee who serves an order without a pickle; you can tell when the cheese is good. Thank you, and I hope this doesn't happen again on my next visit. review_text: Uno de mis macdonals favoritos. Lo k tiene este k no tienen otros es k esta justo al lado de la sagrada familia, los banos suelen estar mas limpios y menos concurridos k los de otros macdobals. La parada de metro de sagrada familia esta justo al lado. Tambien hay una caixa un estanco en la misna calle tb hay burguer king y un poco mas alla kentukym es un lugar ideal como punto de encuentro. Son amables y atentos y tiene terraza importante!!! No recomiendo ir a comer aki xk al estar al lado del templo hay mucha gente. Pero a partir de las 16h se vacia y es un sitio trankilo para merendar o cenar
review_translated_text: One of my favorite McDonald's. What this one has that others don't is that it's right next to the Sagrada Familia. The restrooms are usually cleaner and less crowded than at other McDonald's. The Sagrada Familia metro stop is right next door. There's also a Caixa bank and a tobacco shop on the same street, as well as a Burger King and a Kentucky Fried Chicken a little further on. It's an ideal meeting place. The staff are friendly and attentive, and it has a large terrace! I don't recommend eating here because, being next to the temple, it gets very crowded. But after 4 pm, it empties out, and it's a quiet place for a snack or dinner.

review_translated_text: I'd like to call upon all those who had been stolen inside to jointly claim loss from Macdonald's, which has obligations to ensure the safety of its customers. I was eating in the restaurant, sitting in a corner, when a pigeon appeared out of nowhere. Then, unbeknownst to me, two scammers, under the guise of catching pigeons, stole my Macdonald's phone, which was left on the table. Later, when I reported my phone lost, I discovered it was stolen and the call was from someone in Algeria... First, a warning to tourists: beware of the constant scams in Barcelona! Second, a complaint to McDonald's: no staff member warned or intervened in the scam! They later claimed it was none of their business! Aren't you supposed to provide a safe dining environment when you're dining on your property?! And the strange police station nearby said they didn't have time to investigate and told us to buy a new one.

review_translated_text:

name: Carlos Barros
review_text: Terriblemente malo!!! Pedi un Grand Extreme Bacon&Mushroom. No tenia nada que ver con la foto, incluso lo que mas me choco fue la cuantidad absurdamente pequena de bacon (1 loncha pequena + 1 tirita con 1/4 del tamano de la otra). Presente el caso a un funcionario y luego a la gerente de tienda y me han dicho que tenia ahi 2 lonchas y era lo que tendria de llevar. He sido super educado pero exigiendo mis derechos como consumidor. No demostraran cualquier tipo de comprension o voluntad en ayudar el cliente. Fueran arrogantes y incluso me dijeran que se queria mas bacon deberia pagar un suplemento. No me lo esperaba que pudiera pasar algo asi en un MacDonald's
review_translated_text: Terribly bad!!! I ordered a Grand Extreme Bacon & Mushroom. It looked nothing like the photo. What shocked me the most was the absurdly small amount of bacon (1 small slice + 1 strip 1/4 the size of the other). I raised the issue with an employee and then with the store manager, and they told me they had 2 slices there, and that was all I had to take. I was super polite, but demanding my rights as a consumer. They didn't show any kind of understanding or willingness to help the customer. They were arrogant, even telling me that if I wanted more bacon, I would have to pay extra. I didn't expect something like that to happen at a McDonald's.

review_text:
Disgraceful and disrespectful employee service. A lady dressed in white shirt, I guess the manager didn't believe me when I presented her a salad that was half eaten and had no tuna in it when it was supposed to. She said she couldn't give me another since i had eaten most of it. Should've used my x ray vision first I guess

Didn't argue. Asked for the complaints book. Out came from the kitchen what I guess was the chef. Asked me if i wanted a new salad or just the tuna. I told him tuna and he kept arguing in Spanish w the lady until they finally gave me my salad with the missing tuna on top.

Pretty bad for Macdonalds to have this lady in an executive position

review_text: Este es el mejor McDonalds que jamas he visitado, puesto que puedes acudir a sentarte en una terracita donde poder disfrutar al sol justo a un costado de la Basilica de La Sagrada Familia, una ubicacion totalmente privilegiada, que muchos bares y restaurantes les gustaria tener. Asi que, por el modico precio de un par de EU puedes comer/cenar/disfrutar de un cafe o helado, con unas vistas inmejorables de este precioso e intrinseco edificio. Totalmente recomendable (por lo menos en verano jaja).
review_translated_text: This is the best McDonald's I've ever been to, as you can sit on a terrace where you can enjoy the sun right next to the Sagrada Familia Basilica, a truly privileged location that many bars and restaurants would love to have. So, for the modest price of a couple of euros, you can have lunch/dinner/enjoy a coffee or ice cream, with unbeatable views of this beautiful and unique building. Totally recommended (at least in the summer, haha).

review_translated_text: It's the closest McDonald's to the Sagrada Familia. You have a terrace right in front of the monument. Of course, it's always packed with tourists, but if you order through the drive-thru, it's much faster. Perfect for eating right next to the Sagrada Familia, for a fair price!

name: RAFAEL RUIZ
review_text: A mi McDonald's me gusta, lo unico es que no siempre esta limpio.
review_translated_text: I like McDonald's, the only thing is that it's not always clean.

name: Francisco Morales
review_text: Alguien deberia plantearse eliminar la comida basura del planeta, solo para guiris que vienen a comer mas de lo mismo. Maximo ir dos veces al ano por vuestra salud.
review_translated_text: Someone should consider eliminating junk food from the planet, just for tourists who come to eat more of the same. Go twice a year at most, for your health.
